<h2 class="ui header">
    CALDAM Pre-Conference School on Discrete Mathematics </h2>

<p align="justify">
The school is being organized for PhD students and teachers in computer
science and discrete mathematics during February 5-6, 2015 at IIT Kanpur. This
school is organized jointly by IIT Kanpur, TIFR Mumbai and Charles University,
Prague. The school is sponsored by <a target="_blank" href="http://www.nbhm.dae.gov.in/">National Board
for Higher Mathematics</a>. The school is aimed at fulfilling two purposes:
(i) as a pre-conference school for CALDAM 2015, (ii) as an Indo-Czech Republic
School on Discrete  Mathematics. There are six speakers in
the school, and each of them will deliver a lecture of 1.15hr on an
advanced research topic in Discrete Mathematics. The tentative speakers
of the school are:</p>
<ol>
   <li><a target='_blank' href="http://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~valtr/">Prof. Pavel Valtr</a></li>
   <li><a target='_blank' href="http://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~honza/">Prof. Jan Kratochvíl</a></li>
   <li><a target='_blank' href="http://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~sgall/">Prof. Jiří Sgall</a></li>   
   <li><a target='_blank' href="http://www.math.tifr.res.in/~amitava/">Prof. Amitava Bhattacharya</a></li>
   <li><a target='_blank' href="http://www.math.iitb.ac.in/~niranj/">Prof. Niranjan Balachandran</a></li>
<li> <a target ='_blank' href="www.keralauniversity.ac.in/future/faculty_details.html?id=83">Prof. Manoj Changat</a></li>
</ol>
<p align="justify">
In addition, six speakers mentioned below will deliver lectures of 0:45 hour each on the same
topics mentioned above.</p>
<ol>
<li>Meghana Nasre (IIT Madras)</li>
<li>T. Karthick (ISI Chennai)</li>
<li>Mohit Garg (TIFR, Mumbai)</li>
<li>Sagnik Sen (ISI Kolkata)</li>
<li>Martin Tancer (Charles University)</li>
<li>Martin Balko (Charles University)</li>
</ol>

<h2 class="ui header">REGISTRATION</h2>
<p align="justify">
There is no registration fee for the school. Arrangements
have been made for all speakers and 25 selected participants to stay in
IIT Kanpur guest house, and they will be provided boarding and lodging
free of cost. The registrations is closed now. Selected applicants will be informed by end of November.
</p>

<h2 class="ui header">COORDINATORS</h2>
<ol>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://www.tcs.tifr.res.in/~ghosh/">Prof. Subir Ghosh</a>  (Co-Convener)</li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~valtr/">Prof. Pavel Valtr</a>  (Co-Convener)</li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="https://sites.google.com/site/ambatvijayakumarcusat/">Prof. Ambat Vijayakumar</a></li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://www.nitk.ac.in/show/suresh-m-hegde">Prof. Suresh M Hegde</a></li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://universe.bits-pilani.ac.in/goa/tksingh/profile">Prof. Tarkeshwar Singh</a></li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://maths.uok.edu.in/DrSPirzada.aspx">Prof. Sharief ud din Pirzada</a></li>
  <li><a target='_blank' href="http://cse.iitk.ac.in/users/skmehta/">Prof. Shashank  Mehta</a> (Co-Convener)</li>
</ol>
<h2 class="ui header">FURTHER DETAILS</h2>
<p align="justify">
Contact Professor Subir Ghosh (Email: ghosh at tifr dot res dot in).
</p>


